The instance variable(s) correspond to the propagator setting(s).

execute(spacecraft, start_date=None, out_file_cart=None, out_file_kep=None, duration=1)[source]¶

Execute orbit propagation of the input spacecraft (single) and write to a csv data-file.

The computed satellite states are in the Earth Centered Inertial frame, identical to EarthMJ2000Eq used in NASA GMAT software. For more description see: GMAT CoordinateSystem

Parameters

  • spacecraft (orbitpy.util.Spacecraft) – Spacecraft whose orbit is to be propagated.

  • out_file_cart (str) –

    File name with path of the file in which the orbit states in CARTESIAN_EARTH_CENTERED_INERTIAL are written. If None the file is not written.

    • The first row specifies if the states are in CARTESIAN_EARTH_CENTERED_INERTIAL or KEPLERIAN_EARTH_CENTERED_INERTIAL reference frame.

    • The second row containing the mission epoch in Julian Day UT1. The time (index) in the state data is referenced to this epoch.

    • The third row contains the time-step size in seconds.

    • The fourth row contains the mission duration in days.

    • The fifth row contains the columns headers and the sixth row onwards contains the corresponding data.

    Note that time associated with a row is: time = epoch (in JDUT1) + time-index * time-step-size (in secs) * (1/86400) Description of the data (comma-seperated) is given below:

  • out_file_kep (str) –

    File name with path of the file in which the orbit states in KEPLERIAN_EARTH_CENTERED_INERTIAL are written. If None the file is not written. The output data format is similar to the data format of the out_file_cart file, except the columns headers are as follows:

  • start_date (orbitpy.propcov.AbsoluteDate) – Time start for propagation. If None, the date at which the spacecraft orbit-state is referenced shall be used as the start date.

  • duration (float) – Time duration propagation in days. Default is 1 day.

static from_dict(d)[source]¶

Parses an J2AnalyticalPropagator object from a normalized JSON dictionary.

Parameters

d (dict) –

Dictionary with the J2 ANALYTICAL PROPAGATOR specifications.

Following keys are to be specified.

  • ”stepSize”: (float) Step size in seconds. Default value is 60s.

  • ”@id”: (str) Propagator identifier (unique). Default: A random string.

Returns

J2AnalyticalPropagator object.
